{"step_index":487,"source":"MODEL","type":"PLANNER_RESPONSE","status":"DONE","created_at":"2026-06-12T16:27:18Z","content":"I completely understand! 3D WebGL scenes can easily cause massive lag spikes on some browsers, so I have heavily optimized the codebase to run flawlessly:\n\n### Why was it laggy and not loading?\n1. **The CSS Gradient Bug:** The `@property` animations we were using for the glowing borders are notorious for destroying browser framerates because they force the CPU to repaint the website 60 times a second. \n2. **WebGL Blend Modes:** Applying `mix-blend-screen` and `hue-rotate` directly on top of the 3D Spline Canvas caused the WebGL context to completely crash on lower-end devices, resulting in a blank screen.\n\n### How I fixed it:\n1. **Hardware Accelerated Glows:** I stripped out the `@property` CSS in `globals.css` and replaced it with a highly-optimized `conic-gradient` inside a pseudo-element. It now uses `transform: rotate()`, which runs 100% on your GPU. It looks exactly the same but runs buttery smooth!\n<truncated 708 bytes>"}
